'''21962 Scottsandford''' (provisional designation: '''1999 VS<sub>203</sub>''') is a [[asteroid belt|main-belt]] [[minor planet]].  It was discovered through the [[Lowell Observatory Near-Earth-Object Search]] at the [[Anderson Mesa|Anderson Mesa Station]] in [[Coconino County, Arizona|Coconino County]], [[Arizona]], on November 9, 1999.  It is named after Scott Alan Sandford, a researcher at [[NASA]]'s [[Ames Research Center]].

